## Fix 2: Add Label Input When Linking Stars

### 2.1 Update hook â€” `client/src/components/Universe/hooks/useConstellationLinkMode.js`

Add new state and flow:
- Add `secondStar` state â€” set when user clicks the second star (instead of immediately submitting)
- Add `submitLink(label)` function â€” calls `requestConstellation(token, firstStar.id, secondStar.id, label)` and resets state
- Change `handleStarClickInLinkMode`: when second star is clicked, set `secondStar` and return `{ step: 'enter_label' }` instead of submitting
- Update `linkModeStatus` to include `'enter_label'` when `secondStar` is set
- Update `cancelLinkMode` to also clear `secondStar`
- Export: `secondStar`, `submitLink`

### 2.2 Update Universe.jsx â€” label input panel

When `linkModeStatus === 'enter_label'`, replace the current indicator bar with a label input panel:
- Small floating panel (same glass morphism style as other panels)
- Show selected star names: "Link [firstStar.title] â†” [secondStar.title]"
- Text input for constellation name (placeholder: "Name this constellation (optional)")
- Two buttons: "Create Link" (submit) and "Cancel"
- On submit: call `submitLink(inputValue)`, refetch constellations via camera state change
- On cancel: call `cancelLinkMode`

The `handleStarClick` callback already intercepts link mode clicks â€” when `handleStarClickInLinkMode` returns `{ step: 'enter_label' }`, the star click handler already returns early (no star preview).

### 2.3 Add CSS â€” `client/src/components/Universe/Universe.module.css`

Add styles for the label input panel:
- `.labelInputPanel` â€” positioned center-top (similar to `linkModeIndicator`), glass morphism background, flex column layout, rounded corners
- `.labelInputField` â€” transparent background input, white text, bottom border, no outline
